headline.main: Facts in Relation to the Brig Zebra.

docs.lead_paragraph: To the Editor of the Savannah Morning News: On Saturday, the 15th inst., Lieuts, BURROWE and BELL. of the revenue cutter Hamilton, in company with Mr. A. C. DAVENPORT, called upon the Mayor, and stated to him the situation of the Zebra. The Health Officer was immediately ordered down to ascertain, the condition of the passengers and crew on board said vessel.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. Things in Washington--Speculations and Movements.

docs.lead_paragraph: Senator DIXON, of Kentucky, is in bad health. He leaves for Charleston to-morrow, and will not return this session, having paired off with Mr. BORLAND on the confirmation of BADGER. SAMUEL MEDARY is violently opposed by a portion of the Ohio Democracy in the Cabinet war fare, A strong remonstrance against the bestowal of Executive favor in that direction, has been forwarded from Ohio to Concord.

byline.original: Special Dispatch to the New-York Daily Times:

headline.main: Death of Prof. C. B. Adams.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamer Petrel, which arrived at this port from St. Thomas, W. I., on Saturday, brings the sad intelligence of the death at that place, of Prof. C. B. ADAMS, of Amherst College. Prof. ADAMS had become widely known in the scientific world, by his labors in the departments of Geology; and in his unexpected demise, Science has to mourn the loss of a most indefatigable and accurate investigator.
